{
  "stem": "1581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And another thing that held me back was that by some strange coincidence, I was chosen to be in charge of the medical service of a refugee camp.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[INTERPOSING VOICES]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was a Jewish refugee camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they, they needed a Jewish doctor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Needless to say that after Hitler occupied us, no Jewish doctor was allowed to practice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I was the exception, because I was hired by the Jewish community to take care of the medical needs of this refugee camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The interesting part on this is that when Austria was occupied, a lot of Austrian Jews fled to Czechoslovakia, because we were still unoccupied and free.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they thought they saved their lives by going to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nobody knew what is going-- what the future holds.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a few hundred of these refugees were settled in a old, demobilized factory in a tannery, near Brno, in a little place called Eibenschutz, Ivancice.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was told by the community and also by the SS people, by the Gestapo-- who took over this refugee camp, and from then on it became not a place of help, but a kind of a concentration camp-- they installed me there, as a chief physician.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I must say, it was a very challenging and highly interesting job.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I really liked what I was doing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That brings us to the way how we could endure all this reign of regulation and dehumanization.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was this constant optimism and the constant hope that this is only passing, and we will be all right.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now that I had a job, we somehow settled with a new situation.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in all the future story of the life, this was the-- the leading motif.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
